i do love myself some messy merging

Merge remote-tracking branch 'remotes/origin/master' into Eddie
# Conflicts: # bin/.gitignore # src/MainInit.java # src/gizmos/LeftFlipper.java # src/gizmos/RightFlipper.java # src/model/ProjectManager.java # src/view/RunBoard.java # src/view/RunGUI.java

Merge remote-tracking branch 'remotes/origin/master' into georgios
# Conflicts: # src/MainInit.java # src/model/CollisionManager.java # src/model/ProjectManager.java # src/view/GizmoPanel.java # src/view/RunBoard.java

Started tidying up code.
Collisions work fine, Absorber works fine (integrated jamies code into the Absorber class), Still need to add eddie's flipper stuff, loading works fine
rotating the MIT physics lines and circles isn't fine at all, will need to do some mad math stuff for the MIT bit. since the easiest way to do it is to probably recreate the whole physics path when rotate is called, won't be intensive on the system because it's only called on load.

Changed the ball radius to use standardised L's instead of an arbritrary number
((Board.BOARD_WIDTH / Board.X_CELLS))
is the pixel representation of one L

More tidying, added helper function Board.convertLtoPixels to convert L values into pixel values, changed board from interface to just a standard static value storing class because it was fairly redundant as an interface. could probably consider renaming it to indicate it's a helper class and add another interface that Runboard and buildboard would actually use implemented methods for.
Ball is an abstractgizmo again, still works with everything and code is mostly unchanged.
Flippers still need work, will need to implement what eddie said about having a flipper superclass that gets extended by the left and right flipper class

Made a start converting eddies existing prototype code to stuff that fits better with the current onHit, doTrigger, listener system thing. works for the most part but it keeps overshooting 90 degrees, dunno why, might be something to do with applying at.rotate on the last iteration but not setting the shape to be 90 degrees after the full rotate or something. needs work
uses the flipper superclass for flipper specific storage of stuff like angular velocity and how to differentate between drawing right and left flippers with an xpos modifier in the constructor.
still need to make it update the physics path on every iteration but i'll do that later
also affinetransform is the devil

Physics rotations work now. note that the collisions do actually work with flippers-in-motion but the angular velocity of the flipper in motion needs to be used in the collision code to actually punt the ball properly, right now it just bounces off wherever the linesegment is in the flippers current rotation and continues falling

Finished flipper collisions, works as intended in the spec now.
Flips to the other point when it's triggered, right now it's just triggered on touch but with keypresses hooked in it should be triggered both on push down and release.
note that this waits until fully flipped to either position before listening to another trigger event which still matches spec but is not true pinball machine as in hold key=rotate
i didn't even realise the Geometry library already had a rotate around function oops, rotatePhysicsAroundPoint uses that now

in motion collisions with the flippers kinda work, bit dodgy though because it can't differentiate between clockwise angular velocity and anti-clockwise angular velocity but works for the most part i think
flippers work for the most part but sometimes they move too fast and clip through into the ball, probs something to do with the rotation code i dunno i'll take a look at it
Attempted to standardise ticktime into Board to make it neater. might need looking at later because i think gravity and friction are screwing with the flipper collisions a bit

Changed where the gravity and friction code goes, not major.
there's some really strange stuff going on through. if you set the movetime to 0.05 which should work absolutely fine as per the mit demo and the gif on the page but nah, it goes too fast, triggers stuff to early and just generally bugs out. needs some serious work
